# Expandable component

For the below code, what is the best way to ensure that the Child components are dependent on the Parent component

```html
<Expandable>
	<Expandable.Header> Header </Expandable.Header>
 	<Expandable.Icon/>
    <Expandable.Body> This is the content </Expandable.Body>
</Expandable>
```

To ensure dependency, we introduce a **Context** using `React.createContext()`

```javascript

import React, { createContext } from 'react'

/* 
* Creating a context, 
* is one way to ensure that the child components are dependent 
* on the parent
*/
const ExpandableContext = createContext()
/* 
* Context has a Provider component which
* needs to be wrapped around your Child component
*/
const { Provider } = ExpandableContext

const Expandable = ({children}) => {
  return <Provider>{children}</Provider>
}

export default Expandable
```

