## Using a Set / List

- This is the primitive approach, but it works nonetheless.
- We iterate over the whole linked list and add each visited node to a visitedNodes list or set. At every node, we check whether it has been visited or not.
- By principle, if a node is revisited, a cycle exists!

```javascript
function detectLoop(list) {
  //Used to store nodes which we already visited
  visitedNodes = []
  currentNode = list.getHead().nextElement;

 /**
 * Traverse the list and put each node in the visitedNodes list 
 * and if a node appears twice in the map
 * then it means there is a loop in the list
 */
  while (currentNode != null) {
    if (visitedNodes.includes(currentNode)) {
      return true;
    }
    visitedNodes.push(currentNode); //Insert node in visitedNodes list
    currentNode = currentNode.nextElement;
  }
  return false;
}

