# Solution \#1

## Brute Force Method

This is the simplest way to go about this problem. We traverse the whole list to find its length. The middle position can be calculated by halving the length.
- Note: For odd lengths, the middle value would be,
- mid = length/2 + 1
- Then we iterate till the middle index and return the value of that node.

## Time Complexity
The algorithm makes a linear traversal over the list. Hence, the time complexity is `O(n)`.

```javascript
//Access HeadNode => list.getHead()
//Acess Length => list.length;
//Check if list is empty => list.isEmpty()
//Insert at head => list.insertAtHead(value)
//Delete at head => list.deleteAtHead()
//Insert at tail => list.insertAtTail(value)
//Search for element => list.search(value)
//Delete by value => list.deleteVal(value)
//Node class { data ; Node nextElement;}
function findMid(list){
  if(list.isEmpty()){
    return null;
  }

  let node = list.getHead();
  let mid = 0;
  if (list.length%2 == 0){
    mid = list.length/2;
  }
  else{
    mid = list.length/2 + 1;
  }
  for(i=0;i<mid;i++){
    node = node.nextElement;
  }
  return node.data;
}
```

