# Solution \#2 - Wrapper Custom hooks 

Custom hooks can also be application specific. The following custom hook will toggle expanded state in React.

The `useExpanded` is a application specific custom hook which will handle the logic for the `expanded` state variable, and `useEffectAfterMount` will handle the logic for invoking a callback only after mount.


Note that these custom hooks will pretty much use the same logic as the `Expandable` compound component we had written earlier. The difference here will be wrapping these in a custom hook.

Hereâ€™s the `useExpanded` custom hook:


```javascript
// useExpanded.js
import { useCallback, useMemo, useState } from 'react';

export default function useExpanded () {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false);
  const toggle = useCallback(
    () => setExpanded(prevExpanded => !prevExpanded),
    []
  );
  // Expose the custom function and toggle hook just like a useState hook.
  const value = useMemo(() => ({ expanded, toggle }), [expanded, toggle]);

  return value;
}
```

