# Answer

The Context API is a component structure provided by the React framework, which enables us to share specific forms of data across all levels of the application. It's aimed at solving the problem of prop drilling.

- Component structure API

- Child components within the Context can share their prop values directly

- Solves Prop drilling (top down approach)

- Available for both Stateful (Class) Components as well as Functional Components (**useContext** hook)

![Context API](https://cmichel.io/static/5088656af004c68bc31df9e3990e0340/c31c2/react-context-vs-hoc.png)

---

## When to use Context API ?

- When you need to share global data across components

- You donot use the context if you simple want to pass the props from Parent to Child component

---

## Create a simple Context API

To create a context, we make use of `React.createContext()` method

```javascript
const UserContext = React.createContext(); // Create a component UserContext 
```

Now the Component created as two child components

- **Provider** : Provides the data to its children component

```html
<UserContext.Provider value = {name: `Pramod`}>
......
</UserContext.Provider>
```

- **Consumer** : 

```javascript
const consumerObj = UserContext.Consumer;
```

---

## Practical use of Context API in React

Practically, we only export the `Provider` child component and the `Context` object as part of a Higher Order Component called - `AppProvider`

- We wrap the AppProvider as the main Parent component in our React App
- All structural / Stateful components, will get this value as part of their context object in the constructor
- All Functional components can make use of the AppContext using the `useContext` hook


```javascript
/**
 * PAJ - Creating a Global Shared State using Context API
 * state defined in this AppProvider will be used throughout the context of our application
 */
import React, { Component } from 'react';
export const AppContext = React.createContext();

export class AppProvider extends Component {
    constructor() {
        super();
        this.state = {            
            version:'3.0.1',            
            title:'Quest App',
            themePalette:'light',
            isHeaderSearch: true,
            questionContent: '',
            answerContent: '',
            toggleTheme:()=>{                
                this.setState(prev=>({themePalette: prev.themePalette === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light'}));
            },
            setLightTheme:()=>{                
                this.setState({themePalette:'light'});
            },
            setHeaderSearch:(val)=>{
                this.setState({isHeaderSearch: val});
            },
            addLocalStorageItem:(name, value) => {
                localStorage.setItem(`quest-${name}`, value);
            }, 
            removeLocalStorageItem:(name) => {
                localStorage.removeItem(`quest-${name}`);
            },
            getLocalStorageItem:(name) => {
                return localStorage.getItem(`quest-${name}`);
            },
            addLocalStorageJSON: (name, data) => {
                localStorage.setItem(`quest-${name}`, JSON.stringify(data));
            },
            getLocalStorageJSON: (name) => {
                const data = localStorage.getItem(`quest-${name}`);
                return JSON.parse(data);
            },
            setMarkdownContent: (type, data) => {
                if (type === 'question') this.setState({questionContent: data});
                else this.setState({answerContent: data});
            },
            getMarkdownContent: (type) => {
                if (type === 'question') return this.questionContent;
                else return this.answerContent;
            }
        };
    }

    componentDidMount() {   
    }

    render() {
        return <AppContext.Provider value={this.state}>
            {this.props.children}
        </AppContext.Provider>
    }
}

```

